body:
It seems that the Icarus Verilog is unable to parse some cases of attribute specification which are allowed by the Verilog 2005 standard. 

I prepared some failing cases to demonstrate the issue. For all of them the Icarus Verilog was invoked with the command `iverilog -g2005 <verilog_file>`:

- Attributes on port connections:

Input Verilog code (attrib05_port_conn.v):
```
module bar(clk, rst, inp, out);
  input  wire clk;
  input  wire rst;
  input  wire inp;
  output reg  out;

  always @(posedge clk)
    if (rst) out <= 1'd0;
    else     out <= ~inp;

endmodule

module foo(clk, rst, inp, out);
  input  wire clk;
  input  wire rst;
  input  wire inp;
  output wire out;

  bar bar_instance ( (* clock_connected *) clk, rst, (* this_is_the_input *) inp, out);
endmodule
```

Error message:
```
attrib05_port_conn.v:19: syntax error
attrib05_port_conn.v:19: error: Syntax error in instance port expression(s).
```

- Attributes on function calls (attrib07_func_call.v):

Input Verilog code:
```
module foo(clk, rst, inp_a, inp_b, out);
  input  wire clk;
  input  wire rst;
  input  wire [7:0] inp_a;
  input  wire [7:0] inp_b;
  output wire [7:0] out;

  function [7:0] do_add;
    input [7:0] inp_a;
    input [7:0] inp_b;

    do_add = inp_a + inp_b;
  endfunction

  always @(posedge clk)
    if (rst) out <= 0;
    else     out <= do_add (* combinational_adder *) (inp_a, inp_b);

endmodule
```

Error message:
```
attrib07_func_call.v:19: syntax error
attrib07_func_call.v:19: error: malformed statement
```

